WEBVTT

00:00.011 --> 00:02.662
I don't know, have you
seen <i> Planet of the Apes?</i>

00:02.663 --> 00:05.530
It's like the post-apocalyptic
future down here.

00:05.564 --> 00:07.265
Brenda, relax.

00:07.301 --> 00:09.501
The soup kitchen is
just on the next block.

00:09.536 --> 00:11.603
There have to be easier
ways to spice up

00:11.638 --> 00:12.971
a college
application.

00:13.006 --> 00:14.539
It's all about
community service.

00:14.574 --> 00:16.608
Colleges don't care about
test scores anymore.

00:16.643 --> 00:18.610
Couldn't we have picked
a less creepy community?

00:18.645 --> 00:19.911
Whoa, Brenda,

00:19.946 --> 00:21.179
do you see that?

00:21.214 --> 00:22.934
There's a guy over there
in the storm drain.

00:24.084 --> 00:26.017
He looks
stuck.

00:26.053 --> 00:27.419
Help me get this stuff
out of the way.

00:27.454 --> 00:28.653
Seriously?

00:28.689 --> 00:31.723
Do you want to go
to Harvard or not?

00:31.758 --> 00:33.458
Sir, are you okay?

00:33.493 --> 00:35.126
Does he look
okay, Brenda?

00:35.162 --> 00:36.361
(sighs)

00:36.396 --> 00:38.663
Sir, we're going
to get you out.

00:38.699 --> 00:40.398
Grab the other
side and pull.

00:40.434 --> 00:42.200
One...

00:42.235 --> 00:44.235
two... three!

00:47.007 --> 00:49.140
(screams)

00:50.410 --> 00:52.544
(chittering)

00:57.317 --> 00:58.750
You're right.

00:58.785 --> 01:00.552
This is going to
make an awesome

01:00.587 --> 01:02.387
college essay.

01:08.228 --> 01:10.261
How long have
you been up?

01:10.297 --> 01:11.730
Oh, not too long.

01:11.765 --> 01:13.665
I just wanted to read this
new piece on the Flyers.

01:13.700 --> 01:15.834
I'm telling you, Hextall's gonna win us
the Cup this year.

01:15.869 --> 01:17.435
You didn't sleep again, did you?

01:17.471 --> 01:18.803
I was, uh,
it was in and out.

01:18.839 --> 01:20.138
I was probably just, you know,

01:20.173 --> 01:21.773
getting used to
this new house and all.

01:21.808 --> 01:25.443
Booth, you haven't slept
well in a long time.

01:25.479 --> 01:27.479
I'm worried that
something is wrong.

01:27.514 --> 01:29.414
You were
falsely accused.

01:29.449 --> 01:31.182
You were
in prison.

01:31.218 --> 01:32.984
You've been through a lot.

01:33.019 --> 01:34.019
Well, so have you.

01:34.054 --> 01:35.387
Not as much as you.

01:35.422 --> 01:37.122
Sweets would say

01:37.157 --> 01:38.623
that you have
avoidance issues.

01:38.658 --> 01:40.125
Oh, avoidance issues. What?

01:40.160 --> 01:41.793
You're still
not trusting

01:41.828 --> 01:43.461
the people
you work with.

01:43.497 --> 01:44.863
I'm concerned you're not dealing

01:44.898 --> 01:46.564
with the trauma you suffered.

01:46.600 --> 01:48.633
Listen, Sweets has passed away,
okay? God bless his soul.

01:48.668 --> 01:50.034
And you know what?

01:50.070 --> 01:51.302
You don't even
believe in psychology.

01:51.338 --> 01:52.804
Right?

01:52.839 --> 01:54.105
You know
what, I...

01:54.141 --> 01:55.840
Let's not talk
about this now.

01:55.876 --> 01:57.742
Please?

01:57.778 --> 02:00.378
All right, look,
I'll sleep when I'm tired.

02:00.414 --> 02:02.447
But for now,
I'm gonna make you pancakes.

02:02.482 --> 02:04.616
I know you've
missed my pancakes.

02:04.651 --> 02:06.785
(phone ringing) Yes, you have.
Pancakes coming up.

02:06.820 --> 02:08.686
Booth...

02:08.722 --> 02:10.722
Yeah...
Right, right, okay.

02:10.757 --> 02:12.457
Ooh... on our way.
Sure.

02:12.492 --> 02:15.160
Well, it looks like someone
is sleeping the big sleep.

02:15.195 --> 02:16.895
So much for the pancakes.
They found a body

02:16.930 --> 02:18.663
under the bridge
in Garfield Heights.

02:18.698 --> 02:21.199
I'll get Christine
ready for day care.

02:21.234 --> 02:23.334
(indistinct radio chatter)

02:30.277 --> 02:32.577
SAROYAN: The victim was found by
a couple of high school kids

02:32.612 --> 02:34.078
who didn't realize
the guy was dead

02:34.114 --> 02:37.215
because weasels were
making the body move.

02:37.250 --> 02:38.730
BOOTH:
Whoa, they must've freaked out.

02:38.752 --> 02:40.218
SAROYAN:
Actually, one was pumped.

02:40.253 --> 02:41.886
Said something about it
being what she needed

02:41.922 --> 02:44.189
to get into Harvard?
These trusty hands are all yours.

02:44.224 --> 02:46.558
Put me to work. Aubrey, what are
you doing here?

02:46.593 --> 02:48.860
Well, you know, I was
in the neighborhood and I heard the call,

02:48.895 --> 02:50.829
so I sort of figured
I'd stop by--

02:50.864 --> 02:52.163
holy crap!

02:52.199 --> 02:54.866
(gagging):
Oh, man...

02:54.901 --> 02:56.100
Oh, my God.

02:56.136 --> 02:58.269
Where's the other half of him?

02:58.305 --> 03:00.465
That's the worst thing I've ever seen.
SAROYAN: Really?

03:00.474 --> 03:02.474
I'd only give this about a 7.5.

03:02.509 --> 03:03.942
I'd give this a six.

03:03.977 --> 03:05.343
You know, the floaters
are much worse.

03:05.378 --> 03:06.744
Yeah, well,
you know,

03:06.780 --> 03:08.346
give me a nice,
clean gunshot any day.

03:08.381 --> 03:10.048
It seems you're
not familiar with

03:10.083 --> 03:11.483
the explosive nature of a head wound.
AUBREY: Okay, okay,

03:11.518 --> 03:13.985
hazing the new guy.
It's really funny.

03:14.020 --> 03:15.854
So what the hell happened here?

03:15.889 --> 03:18.289
The victim got stuck in the
drain and animals ate the half

03:18.325 --> 03:19.557
they had access to.

03:19.593 --> 03:20.825
I could see how
he got stuck.

03:20.861 --> 03:22.060
He was obese.

03:22.095 --> 03:23.528
Well, half of
him still is obese.

03:23.563 --> 03:25.864
Blunt surface of
the orbital margins

03:25.899 --> 03:29.367
indicates the victim
is male, Caucasian.

03:29.402 --> 03:31.603
Well, the inside of the pants
confirms the male part.

03:31.638 --> 03:34.005
Ooh, wait a sec.
This is not an accident.

03:34.040 --> 03:35.907
Look at the bottom of his soles.
AUBREY: Totally clean.

03:35.942 --> 03:38.209
Didn't walk here on his own.
It's a body dump.

03:38.245 --> 03:40.745
Or an attempt at
one, at least.

03:40.780 --> 03:43.348
I found our ravenous little culprits!
AUBREY: Oh. Rats.

03:43.383 --> 03:45.617
Never been a fan.
HODGINS: Rats?

03:45.652 --> 03:47.151
Don't embarrass yourself,
Aubrey.

03:47.187 --> 03:48.419
These are stoats,

03:48.455 --> 03:50.021
aka short-tailed weasels.

03:50.056 --> 03:51.756
Anyone have
time of death for me?

03:51.791 --> 03:52.824
Uniformity
in scoring

03:52.859 --> 03:54.626
on the cortical
surface suggests

03:54.661 --> 03:55.960
the stoats are
the lone scavengers.

03:55.996 --> 03:57.328
HODGINS:
And given the level

03:57.364 --> 03:58.663
of predation,
I'd say three days.

03:58.698 --> 03:59.731
I'm gonna see what else

03:59.766 --> 04:00.965
I can find.
Three days.

04:01.001 --> 04:02.267
AUBREY:
His pants are pricey.

04:02.302 --> 04:03.502
This is high-quality
gabardine.

04:03.537 --> 04:04.969
Yeah.

04:05.005 --> 04:06.765
And his shoes are Italian.
Expensive leather.

04:06.773 --> 04:08.072
BOOTH: Well, look,
the big question is

04:08.108 --> 04:09.908
what was Daddy Warbucks
doing down here?

04:09.943 --> 04:11.609
Could've been
buying drugs.

04:11.645 --> 04:13.144
Wouldn't be the first time
in this neighborhood.

04:13.179 --> 04:15.446
HODGINS: Found it!
I found the stoats' den.

04:15.482 --> 04:17.180
And... (grunts)

04:17.216 --> 04:19.284
...it is filled with evidence.
BOOTH: Yeah, music to my ears.

04:19.319 --> 04:21.853
HODGINS: Yeah, no, lucky for us,
the stoat actually

04:21.887 --> 04:24.222
lines his den with
the remains of his prey.

04:24.257 --> 04:25.723
Is that his...?

04:25.759 --> 04:26.624
Hair? Yeah.

04:26.660 --> 04:27.592
And those are

04:27.627 --> 04:28.893
phalanges.

04:28.929 --> 04:30.361
SAROYAN:
And an eyeball.

04:30.397 --> 04:31.963
Oh, God, it's his tongue.

04:31.998 --> 04:34.265
Yes.
Very observant, Mr. Aubrey.

04:34.301 --> 04:35.934
AUBREY: Thank you.
Oh, man...

04:35.969 --> 04:37.201
there's one still inside.

04:37.237 --> 04:39.704
Oh, God... and he's eating...

04:39.739 --> 04:41.906
He's eating, oh, man.
HODGINS: Yeah.

04:41.942 --> 04:43.541
It's a fun job, right?

