05:24.980 --> 05:27.080
I'm seeing numerous
osteophytes.

05:27.116 --> 05:31.017
A common skeletal injury
for the morbidly obese.

05:31.053 --> 05:32.486
Note the perimortem

05:32.521 --> 05:33.787
fractures to the nasal bones.

05:33.822 --> 05:34.955
And also

05:34.990 --> 05:36.623
the anterior
dentition,

05:36.658 --> 05:38.325
the upper left
central incisor

05:38.360 --> 05:39.659
and the lateral
incisor.

05:39.695 --> 05:40.794
SAROYAN:
That would suggest a hard blow

05:40.829 --> 05:43.130
from a right-handed assailant.

05:43.165 --> 05:45.165
But not hard enough to be fatal.

05:47.169 --> 05:48.635
Before we continue,

05:48.670 --> 05:52.105
I would like to...
offer my condolences.

05:55.511 --> 05:57.644
Dr. Sweets was a good man.

05:57.679 --> 06:00.313
Yes, he was.

06:00.349 --> 06:02.549
He was a very good man.

06:02.584 --> 06:03.817
FUENTES: Colleagues can
be like family.

06:03.852 --> 06:05.452
I had an assistant
in Habana, and

06:05.487 --> 06:07.988
like Sweets,
he was like a brother.

06:08.023 --> 06:10.290
Guys, can we please not talk
about Sweets right now?

06:10.325 --> 06:12.125
If we do, we're
going to start crying

06:12.161 --> 06:13.321
and contaminate the evidence.

06:13.328 --> 06:15.295
BRENNAN:
Booth thinks it's odd,

06:15.330 --> 06:18.665
but I find relief when
analyzing decomposed remains.

06:18.700 --> 06:20.700
Yes, Booth
is correct.

06:20.736 --> 06:22.936
All right,
my sartorial work is finished.

06:22.971 --> 06:25.906
This guy is ready
to go freestyle.

06:25.941 --> 06:27.474
SAROYAN:
Discoloration

06:27.509 --> 06:29.743
to the scrotum.
Likely from trauma.

06:29.778 --> 06:31.912
Looks like our killer
fought dirty.

06:33.882 --> 06:35.081
Ms. Montenegro,

06:35.117 --> 06:36.650
it is so good to see you again.

06:36.685 --> 06:38.418
You too, Rodolfo.

06:38.453 --> 06:40.320
What?

06:40.355 --> 06:42.656
He's eye candy.
Just deal with it.

06:42.691 --> 06:44.825
Are you here just to gawk or did
you finish your reconstruction?

06:44.860 --> 06:46.960
Uh, well,
the skull was relatively

06:46.995 --> 06:50.297
unscathed, but before
I add dimension to the face,

06:50.332 --> 06:53.433
I do need an estimate
of the victim's weight.

06:53.468 --> 06:54.835
Oh...

06:56.171 --> 06:57.771
Based on

06:57.806 --> 07:01.107
the measurement of
the bi-iliac breadth,

07:01.143 --> 07:03.210
as well as
the femoral head,

07:03.245 --> 07:05.512
I'd say 136 kilograms.

07:05.547 --> 07:06.780
MONTENEGRO:
So...

07:06.815 --> 07:08.615
factoring in the weight...

07:11.553 --> 07:12.953
SAROYAN:
Oh, no.

07:12.988 --> 07:14.221
It's that guy.

07:14.256 --> 07:15.622
The blowhard.

07:15.657 --> 07:17.424
Is "blowhard"
some kind of a job?

07:17.459 --> 07:18.859
HODGINS:
He was a talk radio host

07:18.894 --> 07:20.093
who was ignorant and angry.

07:20.128 --> 07:21.595
It's a lethal combination.

07:21.630 --> 07:23.296
Well, it certainly
was for him.

07:30.939 --> 07:32.706
Hutch Whitehouse?
He's the victim?

07:32.741 --> 07:34.541
Yeah, do you know him?
Yeah.

07:34.576 --> 07:36.142
His fans are called
Hutchheads.

07:36.178 --> 07:37.477
He's, like, a big-time
conservative talk show host.

07:37.512 --> 07:39.312
Went to UVA
before dropping out

07:39.348 --> 07:40.947
to become a top 40 DJ.

07:40.983 --> 07:42.549
Now he's a right-wing icon,

07:42.584 --> 07:43.984
syndicated nationwide
to the tune of

07:44.019 --> 07:45.452
$10 million a year.

07:45.487 --> 07:47.187
He's pro-guns,
pro-capital punishment,

07:47.222 --> 07:49.456
pro-vouchers,
anti-immigrant, anti-choice,

07:49.491 --> 07:51.892
anti...
Wow. You really know your Hutch.

07:51.927 --> 07:53.627
Nah, I just did a background
check online.

07:53.662 --> 07:55.428
I really want on this case.

07:55.464 --> 07:57.197
Why, because it's a high profile case?
Yeah.

07:57.232 --> 07:59.032
And because he almost
made me throw up.

07:59.067 --> 08:00.667
His remains.
Aubrey,

08:00.702 --> 08:02.235
just put the football down
and go back to your desk.

08:02.271 --> 08:04.070
And, uh, one more thing.

08:04.106 --> 08:05.472
Uh, his wife of 15 years,

08:05.507 --> 08:07.741
Miriam, is waiting
in the conference room.

08:07.776 --> 08:09.142
Okay, all right, you know what?
I'll go talk

08:09.177 --> 08:10.577
to her, you hold on to that.

08:10.612 --> 08:12.212
I could come, too.
Nope, nope. I'm fine.

08:12.247 --> 08:14.114
Are you sure? You
handpicked me, remember?

08:14.149 --> 08:15.715
And Sweets agreed that...
Whoa, whoa, whoa. Wait a second.

08:15.751 --> 08:18.685
Okay, I picked you
to work for me, okay?

08:18.720 --> 08:20.820
Not to be my partner.
Let's not get that confused.

08:20.856 --> 08:22.088
You know,
me being here

08:22.124 --> 08:24.991
isn't the reason
Sweets is gone.

08:26.328 --> 08:29.062
I-I need to go talk
to this suspect, okay?

08:29.097 --> 08:32.032
So you just put that right
up on the wall up there.

08:35.404 --> 08:36.937
You say he was killed
three days ago?

08:36.972 --> 08:38.471
Well, approximately.

08:38.506 --> 08:39.940
See, the Jeffersonian,
they're still trying

08:39.975 --> 08:41.908
to be a little bit
more specific.

08:41.943 --> 08:43.777
So, um...

08:43.812 --> 08:45.445
You never reported
him missing.

08:45.480 --> 08:47.213
You didn't say anything
to the authorities.

08:47.249 --> 08:49.516
Hutch and I...

08:51.019 --> 08:55.088
...lately, we've led
separate lives.

08:55.123 --> 08:57.557
All right, so you were getting a divorce.
No.

08:57.592 --> 08:58.825
God, no.

08:58.860 --> 09:00.493
Just... busy.

09:00.529 --> 09:02.662
Hutch had his show,

09:02.698 --> 09:04.731
and I promote women's rights
issues all over the country.

09:04.766 --> 09:07.801
I was in Charlotte
three days ago.

09:07.836 --> 09:09.736
So you and Hutch weren't on
the same political wavelength.

09:09.771 --> 09:11.671
On some issues
we were,

09:11.707 --> 09:14.708
and some we weren't.

09:14.743 --> 09:16.810
Isn't that the way
it's supposed to be?

09:16.845 --> 09:20.213
Supposed to be, huh?

09:22.951 --> 09:25.418
Searching for a motive.

09:25.454 --> 09:26.686
I understand.

09:26.722 --> 09:27.887
I also stand

09:27.923 --> 09:29.203
to come into quite
a lot of money

09:29.224 --> 09:30.690
now that Hutch is gone.
Yeah, you do.

09:30.726 --> 09:34.027
$30 million worth,
according to this contract.

09:34.062 --> 09:35.729
Some people value
their relationship

09:35.764 --> 09:37.964
more than money.
You're right.

09:38.000 --> 09:40.141
So can you think of anyone who'd
want to hurt your husband?

09:40.142 --> 09:42.502
Half the people who listened to his show
probably wanted him dead.

09:42.537 --> 09:45.038
Right, he was offensive.

09:45.073 --> 09:48.108
You should talk to Bob Gordon,
his producer.

09:48.143 --> 09:49.509
And Alan, his co-host.

09:49.544 --> 09:51.745
They kept track
of all the crazies.

09:51.780 --> 09:54.614
Had to, for insurance reasons.

09:56.218 --> 09:57.517
FUENTES:
<i>All the damage</i>

09:57.552 --> 09:59.119
I found on the upper half

09:59.154 --> 10:00.887
of his remains is superficial.

10:00.922 --> 10:02.622
So you think
cause of death

10:02.657 --> 10:04.724
must be south of the border?
Yes.

10:04.760 --> 10:06.726
Unfortunately, I cannot
clean the bones

10:06.762 --> 10:09.863
until you are done
testing the urine.

10:09.898 --> 10:11.865
That is correct, Dr. Fuentes.

10:11.900 --> 10:13.967
So unless you want to test
the urine yourself...

10:14.002 --> 10:15.402
No, gracias.

10:20.442 --> 10:22.409
Okay. So the first
sample came back

10:22.444 --> 10:25.178
negative for
drugs, alcohol,

10:25.213 --> 10:27.680
no poisons...
Look at his cortisol level.

10:27.716 --> 10:28.882
SAROYAN:
That can't be right.

10:28.917 --> 10:30.150
When someone's
attacked,

10:30.185 --> 10:31.518
their cortisol levels spike.

10:31.553 --> 10:32.752
It's a direct response
to stress.

10:32.788 --> 10:34.654
And his oxytocin
levels are up.

10:36.058 --> 10:38.291
It's like he was
enjoying being murdered.

10:40.395 --> 10:42.395
HUTCH WHITEHOUSE:
<i>Everyone's talking about voter reform.</i>

10:42.431 --> 10:43.963
<i>How about this?</i>

10:43.999 --> 10:45.799
You don't speak English, you don't vote.
Oh.

10:45.834 --> 10:47.167
And those kids sneaking in?

10:47.202 --> 10:49.669
They grow up.
If we starve them out now,

10:49.704 --> 10:51.171
no problem in the future.

10:51.206 --> 10:52.505
There are simple solutions,
citizens.

10:52.541 --> 10:54.274
More guns, not less.

10:54.309 --> 10:55.608
Celebrate diversity?

10:55.644 --> 10:58.478
How about celebrate
our own kind? Huh?

10:58.513 --> 11:00.080
Whoa, whoa, whoa. Shut
that crap off, will you?

11:00.115 --> 11:01.381
Man, that's horrible.

11:01.416 --> 11:02.982
I was hoping you'd say that.

11:03.018 --> 11:04.484
Well, what do you know
about his producer?

11:04.519 --> 11:05.618
Well, his name is Bob Gordon.

11:05.654 --> 11:07.020
And he's a mega-billionaire.

11:07.055 --> 11:09.189
Like the one percent
of the one percent.

11:09.224 --> 11:12.192
He's also a big-time donor to
all the conservative super PACs.

11:12.227 --> 11:14.427
Did he have any beef with Hutch?
No reason to.

11:14.463 --> 11:16.162
Hutch was the golden goose.
He brought in hundreds

11:16.198 --> 11:18.064
of millions in ad revenue.

11:18.100 --> 11:19.365
He does have a record though.

11:19.401 --> 11:20.600
Two DUI's.

11:20.635 --> 11:22.335
One arrest for hunting deer

11:22.370 --> 11:23.570
without a license...

11:23.605 --> 11:25.038
while intoxicated.
Great.

11:25.073 --> 11:26.439
So drunk, armed and dangerous.

11:26.475 --> 11:27.974
What about Hutch's
on-air partner?

11:28.009 --> 11:29.175
Alan Spaziano.

11:29.211 --> 11:30.810
He was Hutch's
on-air punching bag.

11:30.846 --> 11:34.380
Hutch called him a Demo-crap,
one of his go-to jokes.

11:34.416 --> 11:36.049
Does he have a record?
No.

11:36.084 --> 11:39.185
Spaziano's so clean,
he's practically Canadian.

11:39.221 --> 11:40.987
Clean but humiliated.

11:41.115 --> 11:42.982
Sounds like a suspect to me.

11:43.017 --> 11:45.084
Yeah. Thanks for bringing me
along, Agent Booth.

11:45.119 --> 11:46.953
I really appreciate it.

11:46.988 --> 11:49.322
You should.

11:52.393 --> 11:53.926
MAN:
<i>How many times do I have</i>

11:53.962 --> 11:55.528
to say it till it gets
through that thick,

11:55.563 --> 11:57.771
commie skull of yours
that when you're fired,

11:57.772 --> 11:59.004
it means you don't
work here anymore?

11:59.041 --> 12:01.074
I can do the show
on my own, Bob.

12:01.108 --> 12:04.309
I don't need Hutch!
There's no money in liberal talk, Alan.

12:04.346 --> 12:05.912
"There's no money
in liberal talk, Alan.

12:05.947 --> 12:07.347
"And I should know 'cause

12:07.382 --> 12:08.982
all I care about is money."
It depends on who's

12:09.017 --> 12:10.550
doing the talking, Bob.
BOOTH: Okay, break it up.

12:10.585 --> 12:12.385
The two of you,
just get to your corners there

12:12.387 --> 12:14.654
and stop finger-pointing
at each other. FBI.

12:14.689 --> 12:17.424
We've got a few questions
we'd like to ask about Hutch.

12:17.459 --> 12:19.759
You're the producer?
Yeah. Bob Gordon.

12:19.795 --> 12:21.361
When's the last time
either one of you heard

12:21.396 --> 12:22.429
from Hutch?

12:22.464 --> 12:23.763
Three days ago.

12:23.799 --> 12:25.765
Early morning,
Hutch calls in,

12:25.801 --> 12:28.134
leaves some boo-hoo message
on my cell

12:28.170 --> 12:30.036
that he's feeling sick.

12:30.072 --> 12:32.405
So, you're the compassionate type?
Listen, two months ago,

12:32.441 --> 12:35.041
I gave Hutch a mega deal.

12:35.077 --> 12:36.476
Ever since, he's
been acting like

12:36.511 --> 12:38.078
a complete diva.
I went to his house

12:38.113 --> 12:39.946
to drag his butt out of bed,
only he wasn't there.

12:39.981 --> 12:41.291
Okay, great. Do you still
have that voice mail?

12:41.292 --> 12:42.301
I deleted it.

12:42.325 --> 12:44.085
You deleted it!
Well, that's pretty convenient.

12:44.086 --> 12:45.952
Okay, well, I'll tell you what.
Why don't you hand over

12:45.987 --> 12:47.758
your phone so we can help
retrieve those messages for you?

12:47.759 --> 12:49.325
You ever hear
of the Fourth Amendment?

12:49.360 --> 12:51.294
Yeah, it helps with people
who have something to hide.

12:51.329 --> 12:53.729
We can get a warrant, pull it
off your cell company's servers.

12:53.765 --> 12:55.131
I thought the government didn't
bother with warrants anymore.

12:55.166 --> 12:57.633
They just spy
on whoever they want.

12:57.669 --> 12:59.869
You-- Hutch's hobby
was to humiliate you, huh?

12:59.904 --> 13:02.438
Use you as a punching bag.
Hutch was just playing a part.

13:02.474 --> 13:04.140
He doesn't believe
half of what he's saying.

13:04.175 --> 13:06.175
The show is dead
and so is your career.

13:06.211 --> 13:07.743
Yeah. Not much
of a motive, is it?

13:07.779 --> 13:09.278
AUBREY: What about enemies
outside of the station?

13:09.314 --> 13:10.713
His wife said
you had to keep a record

13:10.748 --> 13:12.014
for the insurance company.

13:12.050 --> 13:14.550
Yeah. Be my guest.

13:19.791 --> 13:21.858
Those are just the
credible threats.

13:21.893 --> 13:23.793
Knock yourselves out.

13:23.828 --> 13:25.061
People really hated him.

13:25.096 --> 13:26.629
Yeah, what can I say?

13:26.664 --> 13:28.564
The man was a star.

13:34.741 --> 13:36.374
Dr. Fuentes?
I hear you have

13:36.409 --> 13:37.976
something of interest
to show me?

13:38.011 --> 13:40.178
I'm still cleaning
the southern half of the victim,

13:40.213 --> 13:41.880
but I want you to take a look

13:41.915 --> 13:43.948
at the radius, scaphoid
and trapezium.

13:47.621 --> 13:49.287
Perimortem ligature marks.

13:49.322 --> 13:52.023
The victim was bound
at time of death.

13:52.058 --> 13:54.959
I also found some bilateral
microfracturing on the hyoid.

13:54.995 --> 13:56.761
He was strangled.

13:56.797 --> 13:59.364
Although the pressure
wasn't sufficient to be fatal.

13:59.399 --> 14:00.865
So, still no cause of death.

14:00.901 --> 14:02.167
No.

14:02.202 --> 14:04.335
But I have seen injuries
like these before.

14:04.371 --> 14:07.005
In Habana I was told

14:07.040 --> 14:09.007
to obscure evidence
like this...

14:09.042 --> 14:10.842
after the Rapid
Response Brigades

14:10.877 --> 14:13.111
would interrogate
a prisoner.

14:13.146 --> 14:15.013
The secret police.

14:15.048 --> 14:18.983
Yes. Another reason
why I defected.

14:19.019 --> 14:21.586
These lacerations
to the wrists,

14:21.621 --> 14:23.488
plus the strangulation
and the repeated

14:23.523 --> 14:24.989
strikes to the genitals...

14:25.025 --> 14:27.091
The victim was tortured
prior to death.

14:27.127 --> 14:29.627
Yes. But what was it
they wanted to know?

14:31.000 --> 14:37.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

14:39.506 --> 14:41.272
Wow. All these
boxes are filled

14:41.308 --> 14:42.941
with threatening
letters to the victim?

14:42.976 --> 14:45.009
Yeah, Booth read over everything

14:45.045 --> 14:46.644
looking for potential suspects.

14:46.680 --> 14:48.546
"Booth"? Booth read
through all this?

14:48.582 --> 14:50.348
Hey, I tried to help,
but apparently

14:50.383 --> 14:52.584
Booth's trust
doesn't extend that far.

14:52.619 --> 14:54.485
These are the letters
he thought stood out.

14:54.521 --> 14:56.154
And these are all
from the same guy?

14:56.189 --> 14:58.523
Yeah. I took a quick glance.
I agree with Booth.

14:58.558 --> 14:59.718
Dude was obsessed with Hutch.

14:59.726 --> 15:01.086
Each letter rants
against something

15:01.094 --> 15:02.460
he said on his show.

15:02.495 --> 15:03.495
So, an angry liberal?

15:03.530 --> 15:04.662
You'd think, but no.

15:04.698 --> 15:06.064
Radical conservative.

15:06.099 --> 15:07.999
Thought Hutch was too soft.

15:08.869 --> 15:10.568
Oh.

15:10.604 --> 15:12.370
From the postmark,
I was able to determine

15:12.405 --> 15:14.372
which post office
picked up the letter.

15:14.407 --> 15:16.975
So, it was somewhere
in this area.

15:17.010 --> 15:18.576
Did you cross-reference that

15:18.612 --> 15:20.044
with individuals
with criminal records?

15:20.080 --> 15:21.346
I did.

15:22.582 --> 15:23.915
SAROYAN:
Yikes, 78 names.

15:23.950 --> 15:25.116
Remind me not to walk

15:25.151 --> 15:26.451
in that neighborhood at night.

15:26.486 --> 15:27.986
Yeah, all the letters had pretty

15:28.021 --> 15:31.222
basic grammar and punctuation,
sloppy penmanship.

15:31.258 --> 15:33.224
Yeah, probably no more
than a high school education.

15:33.260 --> 15:36.194
Okay, well, when I eliminate
the college graduates,

15:36.229 --> 15:38.796
I'm left with
a list of 45 names.

15:38.832 --> 15:40.072
Oh, we can get that number down

15:40.100 --> 15:42.100
because the king has arrived.

15:42.135 --> 15:45.003
King of the lab?
Isn't that a little passé?

15:45.038 --> 15:46.738
I found some trace
on the reverse side

15:46.773 --> 15:48.673
of a couple of the letters.
I put it up on the server.

15:48.708 --> 15:50.475
This guy's anger actually
worked well for us.

15:50.510 --> 15:51.743
He pushed so hard

15:51.778 --> 15:52.877
with his pen that the paper

15:52.913 --> 15:54.012
picked up particulates

15:54.047 --> 15:55.680
from the writing surface below.

15:55.715 --> 15:58.016
Asbestos, PCB and lead.

15:58.051 --> 15:59.584
Meaning he is living
in a building

15:59.619 --> 16:01.719
which should be condemned.
Thank you, thank you.

16:01.755 --> 16:03.421
Hold the coronation,
Your Majesty.

16:03.456 --> 16:04.756
All right.

16:04.791 --> 16:07.158
Okay, just look up
buildings in the area

16:07.193 --> 16:09.761
which failed inspection.

16:12.265 --> 16:14.632
SAROYAN:
Wow, okay.

16:14.668 --> 16:15.967
MONTENEGRO:
William Byers,

16:16.002 --> 16:17.902
arrested two years ago
for assaulting

16:17.938 --> 16:20.638
a Muslim with a baseball bat.

16:20.674 --> 16:22.140
All hail the king, baby.

16:22.175 --> 16:24.509
King of the lab!

16:24.544 --> 16:26.077
Oh, boy.

16:26.112 --> 16:27.578
I had a local black and white

16:27.614 --> 16:29.347
confirm that Byers is home.

16:29.382 --> 16:31.482
Yeah, me, too. Heading there now.
Oh, I'll just be a sec.

16:31.518 --> 16:33.418
No, no, no.
Taking Bones.

16:33.453 --> 16:35.286
But the guy's a psycho.
He could be dangerous.

16:35.322 --> 16:37.555
What? You don't think
I can take care of myself?

16:37.590 --> 16:39.190
What? No! But I could help.

16:39.225 --> 16:41.125
I get it that it's tough
to trust somebody new.

16:41.161 --> 16:42.927
But I thought we were really
starting to get along.

16:42.963 --> 16:44.762
Right. That's good.
That is good.

16:44.798 --> 16:47.865
Why don't you let things just,
uh, run their course, okay?

16:47.901 --> 16:50.601
Sure.

16:50.637 --> 16:53.271
BRENNAN:
<i>If Byers is dangerous,</i>

16:53.306 --> 16:54.973
why didn't you bring
Agent Aubrey as backup?

16:55.008 --> 16:56.541
He's a good agent, isn't he?
Look...

16:56.576 --> 16:57.709
Aubrey is fine, okay?

16:57.744 --> 17:00.044
But you, you are my partner.

17:00.080 --> 17:03.348
Your world has to be bigger
than just you and me, Booth.

17:03.383 --> 17:05.683
It is, all right?
I'm back to work, aren't I?

17:05.719 --> 17:07.752
Well, objectively
that's true.

17:07.787 --> 17:09.220
But you still don't seem
to trust anyone.

17:09.255 --> 17:11.155
And you have to,
to do this job.

17:11.191 --> 17:12.522
I trust you.

17:12.559 --> 17:15.159
Then listen to me. Sweets said
that you have to believe

17:15.194 --> 17:17.194
in something again,
something bigger than yourself.

17:17.230 --> 17:18.230
I do.

17:18.263 --> 17:19.731
My family.

17:19.766 --> 17:21.098
You haven't been to church

17:21.134 --> 17:22.214
since you've been released.

17:22.234 --> 17:23.334
You don't even believe in God.

17:23.369 --> 17:24.535
But you do.

17:24.570 --> 17:25.570
And you used to believe

17:25.571 --> 17:27.137
that people were good.

17:27.173 --> 17:28.840
And they deserve to be trusted.
Look, Bo-- let's not,

17:28.875 --> 17:31.175
not now, all right, Bones?
Not when we're about to go

17:31.211 --> 17:33.344
after a murder suspect.
Look, I love you,

17:33.380 --> 17:35.213
but you really have no idea
what you're talking about.

17:35.248 --> 17:37.382
I made a professional call
with Aubrey, that's it.

17:37.417 --> 17:39.884
I am fine.

17:44.324 --> 17:45.390
(muffled music playing)

17:45.425 --> 17:47.458
FBI, Mr. Byers. Open up!

17:47.494 --> 17:48.893
I don't think he can
hear you, Booth.

17:48.928 --> 17:50.728
The music is at
least 85 decibels.

17:50.764 --> 17:53.398
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

17:53.433 --> 17:54.866
If it's safe enough not to bring Aubrey...
Just...

17:54.901 --> 17:56.401
...it's safe enough to enter.

17:56.436 --> 17:58.736
Just stay behind me,
you understand?

17:58.772 --> 18:00.772
Mr. Byers? FBI.

18:00.807 --> 18:03.007
Your door was unlocked.

18:03.043 --> 18:04.609
The music is horrible.
Mr. Byers?

18:04.644 --> 18:06.210
Oh, Booth?

18:07.614 --> 18:08.946
He's ordering fertilizer.

18:08.982 --> 18:10.214
He's making a bomb.

18:11.451 --> 18:12.884
(music stops)

18:12.919 --> 18:14.199
What the hell are
you doing here?

18:14.220 --> 18:15.753
All right, hold it
right there. FBI.

18:17.223 --> 18:19.157
Whoa, whoa, whoa, all right.
All right, easy.

18:19.192 --> 18:20.525
Come on.
Booth,

18:20.560 --> 18:22.126
oh!
(grunts)

18:22.162 --> 18:24.195
Easy. Easy.
All right.

18:24.230 --> 18:26.197
BYERS: I do not recognize
your authority.

18:26.232 --> 18:28.433
(grunting)

18:29.404 --> 18:31.367
So we found your manifesto
in your apartment.

18:31.368 --> 18:32.501
I tell you, there's a lot

18:32.501 --> 18:34.100
of misspelled
words in there.

18:34.136 --> 18:36.536
So now the problem's
believing in the white race?

18:36.571 --> 18:37.398
When it's all the foreigners

18:37.421 --> 18:39.427
that are coming in here
and destroying the country.

18:39.541 --> 18:40.886
Is that who you were gonna make
the bombs for?

18:40.910 --> 18:42.176
You got to open your eyes, man.

18:42.177 --> 18:45.945
The Mexicans are coming in here,
taking our jobs. The blacks,

18:45.981 --> 18:48.648
all of 'em on drugs.
What about Hutch Whitehouse?

18:48.683 --> 18:50.450
The traitor?

18:50.485 --> 18:53.086
Oh, yeah, yeah.
I mean, he talks a good game.

18:53.121 --> 18:54.487
But when I wanted him
to spread the word

18:54.523 --> 18:56.363
about the armed uprising,
you know what he did?

18:56.391 --> 18:58.324
He slithered off
like a little garter snake.

18:58.326 --> 19:00.460
So he doesn't deserve to

19:00.495 --> 19:02.529
much less be the spokesman.
Which is probably why

19:02.564 --> 19:05.965
he was murdered
three days ago, right?

19:07.302 --> 19:09.602
God works in mysterious ways,
doesn't He?

19:09.638 --> 19:11.538
He sure does. So
did you do it?

19:11.573 --> 19:14.674
Did you murder him?
Did you kill him?

19:16.978 --> 19:18.678
Let me tell you something,

19:18.713 --> 19:20.980
I ain't a coward like Hutch.

19:21.016 --> 19:24.350
So, yeah, I admit it. I did it.

19:24.386 --> 19:27.453
And everybody's gonna know
my name. So you can let

19:27.489 --> 19:29.622
everybody know that
that's the future that they have

19:29.658 --> 19:31.658
if they don't support
white America.

19:31.693 --> 19:32.327
You tortured him.

19:32.351 --> 19:34.243
He begged for mercy,
and I didn't give him none.

19:34.663 --> 19:36.623
Just finished him off,
you cut his head clean off.

19:36.631 --> 19:38.064
That's-that's right.
That's how you send a message.

19:38.099 --> 19:39.532
That's how you create a name
for yourself.

19:39.568 --> 19:41.167
You got it. You got it.
I took him by his fat neck

19:41.203 --> 19:43.670
and I sliced deeper
and deeper.

19:43.705 --> 19:45.473
WA... Hey, where you going?
Where you going?

19:45.497 --> 19:46.407
Hey, you know what,

19:46.408 --> 19:48.608
you're lying, okay?
He wasn't decapitated.

19:48.643 --> 19:50.510
S-So, wait, you just gonna...
y-you gonna...

19:50.545 --> 19:52.445
just gonna let me...
let me go?

19:52.469 --> 19:53.180
No.

19:53.181 --> 19:55.682
No, I mean, you were gonna make
a fertilizer bomb. You're just

19:55.717 --> 19:58.017
a pure white terrorist who's
going to jail for a long,

19:58.053 --> 19:59.285
long time,
and I'm gonna make sure

19:59.321 --> 20:01.254
that no one ever knows
your name.

20:01.289 --> 20:03.857
(door opens)

20:13.935 --> 20:16.536
<i>La Tierra llamando</i>
Dr. Brennan.

20:16.571 --> 20:18.638
<i>Por favor...</i>
What, Dr. Fuentes?

20:18.673 --> 20:21.407
I-I was concentrating
on the radius.

20:21.443 --> 20:24.410
're positing
torture, but...

20:24.446 --> 20:26.546
look at the damage
to the radius.

20:26.581 --> 20:29.549
Mmm. I see what you mean.

20:29.584 --> 20:31.351
Compared to what I've seen
in Cuba,

20:31.386 --> 20:33.419
the damage is relatively slight.
SAROYAN: So...

20:33.455 --> 20:35.455
we're looking
for a compassionate torturer?

20:35.490 --> 20:37.223
And look at the pelvis.

20:37.259 --> 20:39.359
There's evidence
of calcification.

20:39.394 --> 20:41.995
Which would suggest that he had
been hit in the <i> cojones</i> before.

20:42.030 --> 20:44.898
Based on the topography
of the calcification,

20:44.933 --> 20:46.833
I'd say multiple times
in the last year.

20:46.868 --> 20:50.003
That might explain
his low cortisol levels.

20:50.038 --> 20:51.738
If he'd been tortured before,
he could become accustomed

20:51.773 --> 20:53.006
to the pain.

20:53.041 --> 20:54.774
Look. Look at

20:54.809 --> 20:56.876
the ligature marks
on the victim's wrists.

20:56.912 --> 21:00.480
Calcification of the
scaphoid and trapezium.

21:00.515 --> 21:03.249
<i>Eres una mujer</i>
<i>brillante y hermosa.</i>

21:03.285 --> 21:05.151
(chuckles) <i>Sí.</i>
Isn't that

21:05.186 --> 21:07.453
what happens when someone's
bound and tortured?

21:07.489 --> 21:11.190
He was tortured.
But it was his choice.

21:11.226 --> 21:13.726
So he was into S and M?

21:13.762 --> 21:16.262
Yes. He enjoyed it.

21:19.034 --> 21:21.067
Booth asked me to look
into Hutch's finances.

21:21.102 --> 21:23.269
I found a lot
of big cash withdrawals

21:23.305 --> 21:25.038
on the nights he wasn't home.

21:25.073 --> 21:26.272
For his dominatrix.

21:26.308 --> 21:28.474
Well, S and M is hip now
apparently.

21:28.510 --> 21:30.710
<i>50 Shades of Grey</i>
is outselling <i> Harry Potter.</i>

21:30.745 --> 21:31.945
Hutch,

21:31.980 --> 21:33.746
h-he was a public figure.
I just...

21:33.782 --> 21:36.382
I can't see him doing the deed
at home or in a hotel

21:36.418 --> 21:38.284
or someplace
where he has no control.

21:38.320 --> 21:39.886
Oh, you're good.

21:39.921 --> 21:42.689
Give me a sec. Hutch had
a loan-out corporation,

21:42.724 --> 21:46.192
and one of the assets was
an office space that's empty.

21:46.227 --> 21:50.330
But for some reason he spent
six grand to soundproof it.

21:50.365 --> 21:52.632
Looks like we found ourselves
a sex dungeon.

21:52.667 --> 21:53.933
You want to tell Booth

21:53.969 --> 21:54.969
or should I?

21:54.970 --> 21:56.169
No, you call him.

21:56.204 --> 22:00.039
It should come
from someone he trusts.

22:02.677 --> 22:05.278
BOOTH:
<i>It's creepy, right?</i>

22:05.313 --> 22:08.081
I mean, sex is about love,
not being tied up and beaten.

22:08.116 --> 22:10.016
I disagree.
What?

22:10.051 --> 22:14.153
Sex and violence are two
of humanity's most primal urges.

22:14.189 --> 22:17.423
An amalgamation of them
is a logical by-product.

22:17.459 --> 22:19.425
Bones, S and M isn't
a peanut butter cup.

22:19.461 --> 22:21.761
It's not two great
tastes that go together.

22:21.796 --> 22:23.463
You enjoy being bitten.

22:23.498 --> 22:24.864
Bi... No, I don't.

22:24.899 --> 22:27.166
When we make love,
sometimes I nibble your ear.

22:27.202 --> 22:30.136
Your response is very positive
to say the least.

22:30.171 --> 22:33.673
Look, a nibble is a lot
different an being whipped.

22:33.708 --> 22:36.042
All degrees
of the same thing.

22:36.077 --> 22:37.777
Look, I think the Inquisition,
you know, would've been

22:37.812 --> 22:39.812
a lot different with
nibbling, if you ask me.

22:43.151 --> 22:45.952
BOOTH (whistles):
Whoa, look at this place.

22:45.987 --> 22:48.421
You could perform
Cirque Du Soleil in here.

22:48.456 --> 22:52.125
There are many
possible murder weapons.

22:52.160 --> 22:57.330
Whips, chains, nipple
clamps, Luna beads...

22:57.365 --> 22:59.065
Ah, you sound excited
there, Bones.

22:59.100 --> 23:01.968
Wha... I'm fascinated,
as a scientist.

23:02.003 --> 23:02.935
Ooh.

23:02.971 --> 23:05.204
Right. Okay.

23:05.240 --> 23:06.773
You know, I can probably
get to two shades

23:06.808 --> 23:08.007
of Grey, but I'm not
gonna be making 50.

23:08.043 --> 23:09.442
I'll tell you that.
There should be

23:09.477 --> 23:10.943
something here that could give
us cause of death.

23:10.979 --> 23:12.845
Look at this in the chair,
it looks like dried blood.

23:12.881 --> 23:15.748
This could potentially be
where he was murdered.

