23:46.014 --> 23:47.246
Okay, can
we move close

23:47.282 --> 23:48.448
into the
victim's skull.

23:50.018 --> 23:51.717
Okay.

23:51.753 --> 23:53.352
Now, I reevaluated
the cracked dentition

23:53.388 --> 23:55.655
and nasal bone fractures
I found earlier.

23:55.690 --> 23:56.956
Originally, I thought

23:56.991 --> 23:58.691
that it was the result
of multiple strikes.

23:58.726 --> 24:00.993
You think a single strike
did all this damage?

24:01.029 --> 24:02.261
I hope so.

24:02.297 --> 24:03.896
Now, it was so much
easier in Cuba

24:03.932 --> 24:05.998
when we could just make up
the evidence we needed.

24:06.034 --> 24:07.567
But since we don't
have that luxury,

24:07.602 --> 24:10.970
please put a ball gag
into the victim's mouth.

24:11.005 --> 24:12.205
Yeah. Uh...

24:12.240 --> 24:13.573
A ball gag...

24:13.608 --> 24:15.842
It's a common piece of
S and M paraphernalia,

24:15.877 --> 24:17.310
but it wasn't
at his office.

24:17.345 --> 24:18.911
I know what a ball gag is,

24:18.947 --> 24:21.814
I just don't have
the graphic in my system.

24:21.850 --> 24:24.050
Oh. How strange.

24:24.085 --> 24:26.519
What about a golf ball?

24:26.554 --> 24:28.020
What about a
squash ball?

24:28.056 --> 24:30.556
That is a much more
accurate facsimile.

24:30.592 --> 24:32.258
Oh, yeah. That's a great idea.

24:32.293 --> 24:34.427
We had a guy die on a squash
court once-- so that's perfect.

24:34.462 --> 24:35.995
I mean, it's
not <i> perfect.</i>

24:36.030 --> 24:37.396
But it's... it's helpful for...

24:37.432 --> 24:38.664
Yeah.
...this.

24:39.734 --> 24:41.601
Okay,
squash-ball gag.

24:41.636 --> 24:44.370
Now, simulate a strike
to the victim's face.

24:44.405 --> 24:46.139
We don't yet have
a murder weapon,

24:46.174 --> 24:48.441
but it's got to be something
flat and hard,

24:48.476 --> 24:49.476
like a piece of tile,

24:49.511 --> 24:50.977
but with
enough force

24:51.012 --> 24:52.545
to fracture the
nasal bone.

24:52.580 --> 24:53.946
Okay.

24:53.982 --> 24:56.048
But it's not gonna be
enough to kill him.

25:02.190 --> 25:04.690
Oh. But, look,
it did kill him.

25:04.726 --> 25:07.293
The nasal bone fractures caused
the victim's nose

25:07.328 --> 25:09.162
to swell and obstruct
the airway.

25:09.197 --> 25:10.197
Right. Yes.

25:10.231 --> 25:12.064
And with his nose swollen shut

25:12.100 --> 25:13.466
and the ball gag in his mouth,

25:13.501 --> 25:14.567
he would have suffocated.

25:14.602 --> 25:16.202
We found cause of death.

25:16.237 --> 25:17.770
But wait.

25:17.805 --> 25:19.885
Why wouldn't the dominatrix
have removed the ball gag

25:19.908 --> 25:22.341
and saved his life?

25:26.238 --> 25:28.241
So, Ms. Skarsgard,

25:28.242 --> 25:30.042
we found your DNA

25:30.077 --> 25:31.343
in Hutch Whitehouse's...

25:31.378 --> 25:32.611
what is it-- dungeon?

25:32.646 --> 25:34.113
I'd call it a
fantasy space.

25:34.148 --> 25:35.514
And of course you
found my DNA there.

25:35.549 --> 25:36.748
I'm not a
housekeeper.

25:36.784 --> 25:38.383
It was Hutch's
job to clean up.

25:38.419 --> 25:39.685
Oh, fantasy space?

25:39.720 --> 25:41.120
Right.

25:41.155 --> 25:43.922
Last year you were arrested
on assault charges.

25:43.958 --> 25:44.990
An angry wife.

25:45.025 --> 25:46.892
I was defending myself.

25:46.927 --> 25:48.460
Well,<i> two</i> angry wives,
it says here.

25:48.496 --> 25:50.195
Wow, you really have
a penchant for violence.

25:50.231 --> 25:52.764
Agent Booth, I'm a dominatrix.

25:52.800 --> 25:54.166
If the rough stuff
bothered me,

25:54.201 --> 25:55.968
I wouldn't be fit to do my job.

25:56.003 --> 25:58.470
Both charges were dropped,
by the way.

25:58.506 --> 25:59.605
Right, maybe not this time.

25:59.640 --> 26:00.939
What is
this about?

26:00.975 --> 26:03.008
Is Hutch pressing charges
or something?

26:03.043 --> 26:04.376
No, Hutch is dead.

26:04.411 --> 26:05.811
He choked on his ball gag

26:05.846 --> 26:07.646
after being smashed
in the face.

26:07.681 --> 26:09.448
Oh, my God.

26:09.483 --> 26:11.216
You really thought
you could get away with it, huh?

26:11.252 --> 26:13.185
You think that...

26:14.421 --> 26:16.989
No. This would not
happen on my watch.

26:17.024 --> 26:18.957
I'm a professional.

26:18.993 --> 26:21.660
Oh, a professional. What, do you
guys have some kind of a union?

26:21.695 --> 26:23.929
I'm a licensed
therapist.

26:23.964 --> 26:25.964
I provided a safe,
reliable service.

26:26.000 --> 26:27.933
Right, so you were
his, um...

26:27.968 --> 26:29.768
(chuckles) ...therapist?
Yes.

26:29.803 --> 26:31.837
Hutch felt great guilt
that he made his money

26:31.872 --> 26:33.639
inciting the worst in people.
Oh,

26:33.674 --> 26:35.040
and your beatings
helped him with that?

26:35.075 --> 26:36.375
I never beat him.

26:36.410 --> 26:37.770
He was disciplined,
which fulfilled

26:37.778 --> 26:39.912
his need to feel punished.

26:39.947 --> 26:41.713
Making progress, too.
I can't believe he's dead.

26:41.749 --> 26:43.081
Progress?

26:43.117 --> 26:44.917
Wow, what-what kind
of progress were you making?

26:44.952 --> 26:46.685
Hutch was thinking
of quitting his show,

26:46.720 --> 26:48.554
becoming a moderate,
a voice of reason.

26:48.589 --> 26:51.590
Agent Booth, I swear, when
I left him he was fine.

26:51.625 --> 26:53.992
He could have released himself
whenever he wanted to.

26:54.028 --> 26:56.094
When you left him-- well,
you left him bound and gagged.

26:56.130 --> 26:58.430
Abandonment was
important to Hutch.

26:58.465 --> 27:01.466
But the handcuffs and restraints
I used had safety releases.

27:01.502 --> 27:05.037
It was up to him to decide
when he had had enough.

27:05.072 --> 27:08.106
I would never
harm a client.

27:12.279 --> 27:14.680
Both distal tibias
and fibulas indicate

27:14.715 --> 27:16.882
he visited this woman
quite frequently.

27:16.917 --> 27:19.251
I should have ruled out
torture much earlier.

27:19.286 --> 27:21.954
Both of us were deceived
by the evidence.

27:22.236 --> 27:23.898
Now Booth needs
more evidence

27:23.899 --> 27:25.632
to tie the dominatrix
to the crime.

27:25.667 --> 27:26.866
Of course.

27:26.902 --> 27:28.802
How is your husband?

27:28.837 --> 27:30.537
Is it difficult for you

27:30.572 --> 27:31.871
now that he has been back?

27:31.907 --> 27:33.139
From prison?

27:33.175 --> 27:35.041
Is this another
attempt to bed me?

27:35.076 --> 27:37.443
Because Booth and I are fine.
No.

27:37.479 --> 27:39.712
Not at all. I just know
the effects of trauma.

27:39.748 --> 27:41.981
My brother was betrayed
by the police he worked with.

27:42.017 --> 27:43.550
Like Booth.

27:43.585 --> 27:45.318
Oh. I'm sorry,

27:45.353 --> 27:48.087
I... I assumed you were...
Oh, please.

27:48.123 --> 27:49.389
You're beautiful, I'm handsome,

27:49.424 --> 27:50.824
misunderstandings like this
are common

27:50.859 --> 27:52.058
between people such as us.

27:52.093 --> 27:53.860
True.

27:53.895 --> 27:55.228
Mm.

27:55.263 --> 27:56.830
What happened to your brother?

27:56.865 --> 27:58.832
Well, he had to learn
to accept that there were things

27:58.867 --> 28:01.301
that were beyond his control.
That's part of life.

28:01.336 --> 28:02.669
So he
accepted the

28:02.704 --> 28:04.170
basic principles
of quantum physics.

28:04.206 --> 28:05.705
He knows

28:05.740 --> 28:07.807
nothing of physics.
But he accepted the basic

28:07.843 --> 28:10.276
principles of the
Callan-Symanzik equation,

28:10.312 --> 28:14.514
which states that expectations
will fail in a quantum world.

28:14.549 --> 28:17.116
Thank you for
that, Dr. Fuentes.

28:17.152 --> 28:19.252
I'm not sure what I did.

28:21.056 --> 28:24.457
There's a tendon fiber
imbedded in the tibia.

28:24.492 --> 28:26.559
I also found a gap
in the cortical bone

28:26.595 --> 28:28.261
near where
the tendon attaches.

28:28.296 --> 28:30.897
The victim was pulled
at the extremities

28:30.932 --> 28:33.600
by a device like a rack.
Did you find

28:33.635 --> 28:35.516
any such device in the
victim's S and M retreat?

28:35.523 --> 28:36.904
No.

28:36.905 --> 28:39.405
Which suggests
perhaps he was seeing

28:39.441 --> 28:41.908
more than one dominatrix.

28:44.145 --> 28:46.312
Mm-hmm.
Yeah, yeah, okay.

28:46.348 --> 28:48.114
Right, thanks.

28:48.149 --> 28:50.116
Yeah, that was Bones.
She-She was

28:50.151 --> 28:53.219
saying that the, uh, the body
was, uh, stretched or something.

28:53.255 --> 28:55.955
You know? But it couldn't
have happened in that room.

28:55.991 --> 28:59.023
You know, maybe it was...
was, uh, another dominatrix.

28:59.024 --> 28:59.856
Yeah, or his wife.

28:59.880 --> 29:01.351
No, no, not the wife.
She was out of town.

29:01.351 --> 29:03.952
Yeah, but I talked to the
front desk clerk at the hotel

29:03.987 --> 29:05.985
in Charlotte where she was
staying when he was killed.

29:05.986 --> 29:08.420
And the alibi-- did it stick?
Yes and no.

29:08.455 --> 29:09.888
Uh, we should bring
her in. And when we do,

29:09.923 --> 29:11.923
I want to be there
for the interrogation.

29:11.958 --> 29:13.391
Oh, you want to be there?

29:13.427 --> 29:15.059
Well, you can't
always get what you want.

29:15.095 --> 29:16.828
That's a Rolling Stones song.

29:16.863 --> 29:19.303
You should keep playing that in
your head over and over again.

29:19.332 --> 29:22.033
(laughs) You are an idiot,
you know that?

29:22.068 --> 29:24.569
Excuse me?
Do you really think

29:24.604 --> 29:26.237
you're gonna do
better than me?

29:26.273 --> 29:27.939
You should get out while you can.
Look,

29:27.974 --> 29:31.276
I know that what happened
to you is messed up.

29:31.311 --> 29:33.311
And then what
happened to Sweets.

29:33.346 --> 29:36.147
But remember

29:36.183 --> 29:39.417
that Sweets trusted
me to work with you.

29:39.453 --> 29:41.453
So when you treat
me like crap,

29:41.488 --> 29:43.655
you're treating
Sweets like crap, too.

29:47.828 --> 29:50.995
Here's everything I got
from talking to the hotel.

29:53.166 --> 29:55.633
Good luck with the wife.

29:59.973 --> 30:02.307
I don't know what the fuss
is all about-- so I requested

30:02.342 --> 30:04.742
a ground floor room at my hotel.
Lots of people do that.

30:04.778 --> 30:06.578
Right, but they usually don't
threaten the front desk until

30:06.613 --> 30:08.813
they get that room. Why
was that so important?

30:08.849 --> 30:11.282
I did not kill my husband.

30:11.318 --> 30:13.785
Oh, no, you just wanted a room
right near the exit, right?

30:13.820 --> 30:15.687
So, what, you could sneak
out, go to the movies

30:15.722 --> 30:17.196
and come back without
anyone knowing?

30:17.220 --> 30:19.161
I was in that hotel room
all night long.

30:19.162 --> 30:20.158
That doesn't clear you,
you know? If you were

30:20.193 --> 30:22.193
seeing another man, you're
gonna want your husband dead.

30:22.229 --> 30:24.195
I was not having an affair.
That's how Hutch

30:24.231 --> 30:26.865
dealt with his problems. I tried
to help him so that he wouldn't

30:26.900 --> 30:28.967
have to get slapped around
or whatever

30:29.002 --> 30:31.503
it was that he did.
So you know about the dominatrix?

30:31.538 --> 30:33.505
I know that Hutch was miserable.

30:33.540 --> 30:35.406
He hated the work he was doing.

30:35.442 --> 30:38.042
I tried to help him,
but all he wanted was her.

30:38.078 --> 30:40.411
Anger. Another motive.

30:43.683 --> 30:46.718
That night...

30:46.753 --> 30:48.119
I was dealing with things

30:48.154 --> 30:50.088
my way.

30:50.123 --> 30:52.991
I needed
that room

30:53.026 --> 30:55.093
so that I could buy drugs

30:55.128 --> 30:58.096
without anyone seeing me.

30:58.131 --> 31:00.131
It would've ruined Hutch
if I got caught.

31:00.166 --> 31:02.233
Drugs? Okay, I'm gonna need
the name of that dealer.

31:02.269 --> 31:04.102
I don't know his name.
And it wouldn't

31:04.137 --> 31:06.371
matter if I did, because
I don't have an alibi.

31:06.406 --> 31:09.107
Not until 8:00 a.m.
the next morning.

31:09.142 --> 31:10.708
You have to believe me.

31:10.744 --> 31:12.143
I have a problem.

31:12.178 --> 31:13.578
Yes, you have a problem.

31:13.613 --> 31:16.881
And you have a big problem.

31:18.151 --> 31:20.051
FUENTES:
<i>I reevaluated</i>

31:20.086 --> 31:22.720
the tears to the victim's
tibias and fibulas.

31:22.756 --> 31:25.623
The ones we thought
were caused by stretching?

31:25.659 --> 31:28.893
Yes. The problem I discovered
was the lack of resistance

31:28.929 --> 31:30.762
from any of the surrounding
tendons or cartilage.

31:30.797 --> 31:32.463
I thought it was because
he was unconscious.

31:32.499 --> 31:34.899
Even unconscious,
the body exhibits

31:34.935 --> 31:37.268
an involuntary resistance
to injury.

31:37.304 --> 31:40.371
Which is what I explained to the
good doctor. He had to be dead

31:40.407 --> 31:41.237
for the injuries to occur.

31:41.260 --> 31:43.260
So the stretching
was caused when his body

31:43.343 --> 31:44.976
was moved under the
bridge for disposal.

31:45.011 --> 31:47.445
Dragging wouldn't have
caused the injury.

31:47.480 --> 31:48.880
But suspending him would,

31:48.915 --> 31:50.882
if he was upside down
with his full weight

31:50.917 --> 31:53.651
pulling his tendons taut.
So how does someone move

31:53.687 --> 31:56.220
a man the size of a small
elephant? Well, I went back

31:56.256 --> 31:59.290
and I checked our victim's socks
and the cuffs on his pants.

31:59.326 --> 32:02.427
He really is quite brilliant.
As are you, Doctor.

32:02.462 --> 32:03.528
Thank you.
I'm waiting.

32:03.552 --> 32:04.195
Right, right.

32:04.197 --> 32:06.230
So I found animal
hair. Some weasel,

32:06.266 --> 32:08.466
but mostly white tail deer,
which at first was confusing,

32:08.501 --> 32:11.069
'cause I thought, Bambi, why are
you an accomplice to a murder?

32:11.104 --> 32:13.471
Of course.
The killer used

32:13.506 --> 32:15.707
a deer hoist to move the victim.

32:15.742 --> 32:17.008
That's right.
What is a deer hoist?

32:17.043 --> 32:18.409
It, uh...
Hunters use them

32:18.445 --> 32:19.944
in order to hang
and transport

32:19.980 --> 32:21.613
the deer that they've
shot. But now

32:21.648 --> 32:23.681
we got to figure out who uses...
We already have.

32:23.717 --> 32:27.285
Hutch Whitehouse's producer
is a deer hunter.

32:33.218 --> 32:35.209
So we recovered Hutch's blood from your truck.

32:35.210 --> 32:36.825
I'm a hunter, there's no secret

32:36.826 --> 32:39.293
about that. If you found blood,
it would have been deer blood.

32:39.329 --> 32:41.395
I loved Hutch.

32:41.431 --> 32:43.064
Based on
your views

32:43.099 --> 32:46.400
of climate change, I know
that science is not your forte,

32:46.436 --> 32:49.704
but trust me, the blood work
is incontrovertible.

32:49.739 --> 32:51.038
Well, maybe, uh,
someone took my truck.

32:51.074 --> 32:52.306
It was the middle
of the night.

32:52.342 --> 32:53.808
You seriously want
to go with that?

32:53.843 --> 32:55.409
'Cause the prosecutor
is gonna make

32:55.445 --> 32:58.446
your life a living hell
if you go with that story, pal.

33:02.151 --> 33:04.085
Fine.

33:04.120 --> 33:07.121
I admit it. I did it.

33:07.156 --> 33:09.790
I disposed of the body,
but I did not kill Hutch.

33:09.826 --> 33:12.526
Why would I?
Why? Because Hutch was gonna quit.

33:12.562 --> 33:14.084
Okay, and he wasn't following
your little party line.

33:14.109 --> 33:15.131
Please.

33:15.131 --> 33:17.598
There never was any party line.

33:17.634 --> 33:18.899
That was just a way
of making money.

33:18.935 --> 33:20.935
Hutch would have been
a damn Bolshevik

33:20.970 --> 33:22.270
if it paid well enough.

33:22.305 --> 33:23.604
So would I.
Oh, that gives you

33:23.640 --> 33:24.905
a good motive.

33:24.941 --> 33:26.607
You were going
to lose advertisers.

33:26.643 --> 33:29.043
So I'm guilty of being a
money-grubbing hypocrite.

33:29.078 --> 33:30.411
If that's against the law, then,

33:30.446 --> 33:32.213
throw me in jail,
throw away the key,

33:32.248 --> 33:34.782
but everything else
that I told you was the truth.

33:34.817 --> 33:37.051
After I got his message,
went to his house.

33:37.086 --> 33:38.586
Have it out with
him...<i> verbally.</i>

33:38.621 --> 33:40.788
But he wasn't there.

33:40.823 --> 33:42.189
So I called Miriam.

33:42.225 --> 33:43.958
Wait a second.
You talked to his wife?

33:43.993 --> 33:47.128
Yeah. She told me
about his other place.

33:47.163 --> 33:49.497
And that is where
I found him.

33:49.532 --> 33:51.799
Dead.

33:51.834 --> 33:56.804
Handcuffs, leather, ball gag.
It was revolting.

33:59.842 --> 34:00.841
I could not let the cops
Because it would have

34:00.877 --> 34:01.942
destroyed your station.

34:01.978 --> 34:04.111
Yeah.
BRENNAN: So you dressed him

34:04.147 --> 34:06.947
in his regular clothes and
took him to the storm drain.

34:06.983 --> 34:08.967
How was I supposed to know
that he wouldn't fit?

34:08.991 --> 34:09.985
Again,

34:09.985 --> 34:13.987
science and math would have
helped you a great deal.

34:20.330 --> 34:22.730
Okay, so the producer told us

34:22.764 --> 34:25.099
he threw these down
another storm drain.

34:25.134 --> 34:27.501
The good news is,
the bag was tied shut,

34:27.536 --> 34:29.837
so the evidence is pristine.

34:29.871 --> 34:31.339
There's lots of
blood on this stuff.

34:31.373 --> 34:32.973
Probably from Hutch,
but I can see

34:33.009 --> 34:34.809
if any of it came
from the killer.

34:34.844 --> 34:39.679
Oh, there's a shard of something
imbedded in the ball gag.

34:43.518 --> 34:46.587
May I?
Mm-hmm.

34:46.621 --> 34:50.123
It's a splinter from a fractured
upper left central incisor.

34:50.121 --> 34:52.047
Wow, it would have taken
a lot of force

34:52.072 --> 34:53.806
to break it off
and imbed it in the bone.

34:54.097 --> 34:56.897
More than a blow from a fist.
I believe so, yes.

34:56.933 --> 35:00.000
I am going to measure
the width of the shard,

35:00.036 --> 35:02.436
and perhaps we can build
a profile of the weapon.

35:02.472 --> 35:06.107
7.5 millimeters.

35:06.142 --> 35:08.242
And the ancillary fractures,

35:08.277 --> 35:11.779
I determined the length of what
struck him was 123 millimeters.

35:11.814 --> 35:14.181
So, he was hit
with something

35:14.217 --> 35:16.117
roughly the size
of a pack of cards?

35:16.152 --> 35:17.551
Let me see the tooth.

35:17.587 --> 35:20.321
Looks like there's some kind
of trace on it.

35:20.356 --> 35:21.956
(computer whirring and chirping)

35:21.991 --> 35:26.327
Yeah, there's, like, an
accumulation of textile fibers.

35:26.362 --> 35:29.563
Lint. It's simpler
to say "lint."

35:29.599 --> 35:31.298
Right. Okay, so we're looking
for something

35:31.334 --> 35:32.633
hard enough to crack bone,

35:32.668 --> 35:34.702
about the size
of a deck of cards,

35:34.737 --> 35:36.237
plus lint.
The killer

35:36.272 --> 35:38.506
could have been carrying
something in his pocket.

35:38.541 --> 35:41.609
A cell phone?

35:43.045 --> 35:44.979
MONTENEGRO:
<i>I was isolating</i>

35:45.014 --> 35:46.781
the ambient noise
on the voice mail,

35:46.816 --> 35:49.683
trying to figure out where Hutch
was when he placed this call.

35:49.719 --> 35:51.652
It wasn't his
S and M room?

35:51.687 --> 35:54.088
It should have been
to fit in with the timeline,

35:54.123 --> 35:55.890
but, no, it wasn't.

35:55.925 --> 35:58.959
I'm so impressed you were able
to pinpoint an exact location

35:58.961 --> 36:00.761
from a handful
disparate sounds

36:00.797 --> 36:03.357
Uh, actually,
I-I couldn't do that.

36:03.366 --> 36:04.732
Oh.

36:04.767 --> 36:06.200
No need to worry.

36:06.235 --> 36:08.536
You are still a valued
member of our team.

36:08.571 --> 36:10.638
I'm not finished yet, sweetie.

36:10.673 --> 36:12.473
A twist? Please continue.

36:12.508 --> 36:14.275
So, uh, I realized

36:14.310 --> 36:16.010
that I shouldn't
have been focusing

36:16.045 --> 36:19.079
on the background noise at all,
but rather, the message itself.

36:19.115 --> 36:20.481
Hmm.

36:20.516 --> 36:22.283
HUTCH:
Hey, Bob, it's Hutch.

36:22.318 --> 36:25.319
I'm not feeling too well,
so I won't be coming in.

36:25.354 --> 36:27.087
I'll call you later on.

36:27.123 --> 36:30.691
Now, listen to this sound file
that I pulled off Hutch's show.

36:30.726 --> 36:33.360
Hello, caller. This is Hutch.

36:33.396 --> 36:35.162
What's your question?

36:35.198 --> 36:37.932
Same person.
That's not a twist.

36:37.967 --> 36:39.467
Well, it's not
the same person.

36:39.502 --> 36:43.137
That <i> is</i> a twist.
Listen to this.

36:43.172 --> 36:45.639
MAN:
Hey, caller, let me tell you why

36:45.675 --> 36:48.742
the right is dead wrong
when it comes to guns.

36:48.778 --> 36:50.945
Well, that doesn't sound
anything like the victim.

36:50.980 --> 36:54.215
It's the victim's co-host,
Alan Spaziano.

36:54.250 --> 36:56.717
Now look what happens
when I run all three recordings

36:56.752 --> 36:59.954
through the voice
recognition software.

36:59.989 --> 37:01.589
So, I found clear deviations

37:01.624 --> 37:04.825
on the pitch and tone in
both of Hutch's voice files.

37:04.861 --> 37:06.327
But the pitch and tone were

37:06.362 --> 37:08.429
a perfect match
for Alan Spaziano.

37:08.464 --> 37:09.797
Spaziano pretended
to be Hutch

37:09.832 --> 37:11.232
in order to obfuscate
time of death?

37:11.267 --> 37:14.869
And to give himself
an airtight alibi.

37:18.088 --> 37:19.587
Uh, Bones, come on.

37:19.622 --> 37:20.966
Spaziano's waiting.
You ready to go in?

37:20.966 --> 37:21.718
I'm not going in.

37:21.742 --> 37:23.036
Whoa. What do you mean
you're not going in?

37:23.037 --> 37:24.771
You're not needed
at the lab, okay?

37:24.806 --> 37:26.439
You have everything
we need to nail him.

37:26.474 --> 37:27.807
I agree. I've gone over all

37:27.842 --> 37:29.475
the forensic evidence
with Agent Aubrey.

37:29.511 --> 37:31.944
Remember it's pronounced
"Albi-cans," not "kahn."

37:31.980 --> 37:32.986
What if I just say "thrush"?

37:33.010 --> 37:35.269
No, no. I will not have
my science dumbed down

37:35.283 --> 37:38.017
just because you don't
know Latin, is that clear?

37:38.052 --> 37:39.386
Excuse me for one second.
I need to talk to you.

37:39.410 --> 37:40.120
What?

37:40.121 --> 37:41.621
You're not a shrink, okay?

37:41.656 --> 37:43.656
Just stick to bones
and stuff that you know.

37:43.691 --> 37:45.391
I am using what
I know Booth.

37:45.427 --> 37:47.760
As an anthropologist, I
understand the danger inherent

37:47.796 --> 37:49.662
in making your
world too small.

37:49.697 --> 37:52.532
After times of national
trauma, many countries

37:52.567 --> 37:53.866
become isolationist.

37:53.902 --> 37:55.935
It happened in Japan
with the <i> sakoku</i> policy,

37:55.970 --> 37:57.603
the United States
after World War I.

37:57.639 --> 37:59.539
Would you stop? This is not
time for a history lesson.

37:59.574 --> 38:01.040
There is someone in there
we need to interrogate.

38:01.075 --> 38:02.341
Now let's...

38:02.377 --> 38:04.043
BRENNAN:
This is <i> precisely</i> the time.

38:04.078 --> 38:06.946
Those countries needed
time to rebuild,

38:06.981 --> 38:09.782
but then, eventually, they
had to reengage and recognize

38:09.818 --> 38:12.084
that they had allies
they could trust.

38:12.120 --> 38:16.322
You do, too. You can
trust him, Booth.

38:16.357 --> 38:19.525
I know a good man
when I see one.

38:21.095 --> 38:24.630
I picked you, didn't I?

38:27.001 --> 38:29.368
I'll meet you at home.

38:29.404 --> 38:31.938
(sighs)

38:34.676 --> 38:36.776
Yup, yup, I know.

38:36.811 --> 38:38.611
Back to my desk.

38:38.646 --> 38:42.281
Would you get your ass
in here, okay?

38:42.317 --> 38:44.684
What was it, uh, "kahn"?
Right? Is that what she said?

38:44.719 --> 38:47.553
No, cans, cans, cans, cans.
Cans.

38:47.589 --> 38:49.355
BOOTH: Look, we know that the
call from Hutch was

38:49.390 --> 38:50.957
actually you.
(laughs airily)

38:50.992 --> 38:52.425
I was just messing
with Bob.

38:52.460 --> 38:53.826
I mean, that's all.

38:53.862 --> 38:55.795
You can't arrest me
because I can do voices.

38:55.830 --> 38:58.431
True. That's why we
arrested you for murder.

38:58.466 --> 39:01.000
Why would I kill Hutch? Without
him, my career is finished.

39:01.035 --> 39:02.635
Well, I couldn't agree
with you more, right?

39:02.670 --> 39:04.303
Which is why you used
your cell phone to video

39:04.339 --> 39:05.905
Hutch in his S and M gear.
So you could

39:05.940 --> 39:07.340
blackmail him,
force him to stay on the show.

39:07.375 --> 39:08.641
What you didn't realize was

39:08.676 --> 39:10.810
the handcuffs had
a safety release.

39:10.845 --> 39:12.645
When Hutch saw you,
he freed himself and attacked.

39:12.680 --> 39:14.814
That's when you struck him in
the face with your cell phone,

39:14.849 --> 39:17.350
causing Hutch to drown
in his own blood.

39:17.385 --> 39:19.252
You have no proof of anything
you just said.

39:19.287 --> 39:20.987
BOOTH:
Oh, no. Actually, we do.

39:21.022 --> 39:22.989
Right? I mean, we found bacteria
on the victim's tooth

39:23.024 --> 39:24.524
that was transferred
from your phone.

39:24.559 --> 39:28.027
Disgusting fact-- cell
phones carry ten times

39:28.062 --> 39:29.362
more bacteria
than a toilet seat.

39:29.397 --> 39:31.097
Your wife is a
fountain of information.

39:31.132 --> 39:37.103
Yup. Among the bacteria we
found was one called <i> Candida</i>

39:37.138 --> 39:41.474
<i>albicans.</i> It causes
blotches on the gums.

39:41.509 --> 39:44.977
Look, all we got to do is just
swab your gums, match your DNA,

39:45.013 --> 39:46.946
and that's all
the proof we need.

39:54.689 --> 39:58.958
It was an accident.

39:58.993 --> 40:01.994
I didn't know
that he was going to attack me.

40:02.030 --> 40:03.996
I was trying to save my job.

40:04.032 --> 40:05.498
I'm not a violent person.

40:05.533 --> 40:06.999
I'm anti-guns.

40:07.035 --> 40:08.768
I'm against the death penalty.

40:08.803 --> 40:11.737
This is not who I am.

40:11.773 --> 40:13.272
It was an accident!

40:13.308 --> 40:14.774
(door opens)

40:14.809 --> 40:18.644
It was an...
it was an accident.

40:36.631 --> 40:38.864
♪ I got you... ♪

40:38.900 --> 40:40.833
BRENNAN:
<i>DNA is a match,</i>

40:40.868 --> 40:42.702
so conviction is assured.

40:42.737 --> 40:45.171
All right, so, since you
weren't in interrogation,

40:45.206 --> 40:47.807
you're not gonna get one of
these, I don't think, huh?

40:47.842 --> 40:51.143
Us sharing a celebratory drink
is never contingent

40:51.179 --> 40:53.446
on my presence
at time of arrest.

40:53.481 --> 40:55.648
Besides, I'm not sure you...

40:55.683 --> 40:57.216
I want whatever it is
you're making.

40:57.251 --> 40:58.651
Let me give you a little
taste. You're gonna love it.

40:58.686 --> 41:00.086
It's called a B&B.

41:00.121 --> 41:01.754
Oh. You named it after us?

41:01.789 --> 41:03.022
Beer and bourbon.

41:03.057 --> 41:04.757
I'm kidding.

41:04.792 --> 41:07.360
Just, go ahead, try it out.
You'll love it, all right?

41:07.395 --> 41:09.862
Just expand your world.

41:12.166 --> 41:13.726
That's excellent.
It's excellent, right?

41:13.735 --> 41:15.768
I-I mean, 'cause
it's got a little...

41:15.803 --> 41:17.470
It's got some
tequila in there.

41:17.505 --> 41:19.872
A little ginger beer, some
creme DE cassis. I mean,

41:19.907 --> 41:21.947
it's-it's a weird combination,
but it works somehow.

41:21.976 --> 41:23.542
Like us.

41:23.578 --> 41:26.145
Like us. Shake it, baby.

41:26.180 --> 41:27.813
(laughing)
(knocking)

41:27.849 --> 41:29.315
Are you expecting someone?

41:29.350 --> 41:30.816
No. Are you?

41:30.852 --> 41:33.686
No.

41:36.290 --> 41:39.592
Aubrey, come on in.
I come bearing gifts.

41:39.627 --> 41:42.395
Or <i> gift</i> actually.
I wasn't sure

41:42.430 --> 41:43.562
if you guys were
wine drinkers,

41:43.598 --> 41:46.032
but I, uh, just wanted
to say thanks

41:46.067 --> 41:48.367
to both of you
for letting me join the team.

41:48.403 --> 41:51.003
Uh, means a lot.
Look at that, huh?

41:51.039 --> 41:54.040
Wow, a whole $9.99 worth.

41:54.075 --> 41:55.608
Which is a lot
given his salary.

41:55.643 --> 41:57.243
Very understanding.

41:57.278 --> 41:58.944
Come on in, huh? I'll make
you a drink. Come on.

41:58.980 --> 42:00.346
I'm good. I'm good.

42:00.381 --> 42:02.261
Yeah, I can be obnoxious
when I drink, you know.

42:02.283 --> 42:04.483
Don't want to screw up
a good thing here, so,

42:04.519 --> 42:06.352
just gonna
take it slow.

42:06.387 --> 42:08.120
Yeah. See you tomorrow.

42:08.156 --> 42:09.655
Yeah. Tomorrow.

42:09.691 --> 42:11.557
BRENNAN:
Thank you.

42:11.592 --> 42:14.427
Good night.

42:14.462 --> 42:17.096
(door closes) You know what?
You were right about him.

42:17.131 --> 42:19.298
He was good.

42:19.333 --> 42:21.067
I mean, he <i> is</i> good.

42:21.102 --> 42:22.635
You know what he told me?

42:22.670 --> 42:24.770
He thinks you're the best
agent in the department.

42:24.806 --> 42:26.305
And I agreed with him.

42:26.340 --> 42:28.007
Oh, okay, so that's
how you want it now.

42:28.042 --> 42:30.309
I get it. You in the lab,
me out in the field with him.

42:30.344 --> 42:31.811
Was he that good?

42:31.846 --> 42:34.246
Yeah. You know
what? He <i> was</i> good.

42:34.282 --> 42:36.182
And of course,
I handpicked him.

42:36.217 --> 42:37.616
But we're still partners.

42:37.652 --> 42:40.453
You still need me, right?

42:40.488 --> 42:42.621
Oh, someone sounds
a little insecure.

42:43.279 --> 42:44.305
Are you teasing me?

42:44.305 --> 42:46.319
No. What? Am I? No.

42:46.320 --> 42:48.151
Stop, Booth. Just make me
another drink.

42:48.151 --> 42:50.752
Another drink?

42:50.787 --> 42:52.353
Stop, Booth!
Come on.

